<?xml version="1.0"?>
<html>
  <problem>
    
      <p>A small ball of mass m is suspended on a light long string of length l. Initially, the string makes the angle &#x3B8; with the vertical and the ball is held at rest. The ball is then released. 
</p>
      <br/>
    
    <img width="738" alt="BK143" encrypturl="no" src="/static/problems/MIT/rayyan/check_points/Pictures/BK143.png"/>
    <parameter default="2" description="Maximum Number of Tries" type="int_pos" name="maxtries" loncapaid="11">
      
        <p>
      <br/>
Part 1. 
In order to find the tension of the string at the moment when the ball passes its lowest position, which concepts/ideas are most useful?
</p>
      
      <part loncapaid="12">
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="13" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                  Constant-acceleration kinematics and conservation of energy.
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                  Constant-acceleration kinematics and conservation of momentum.
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                  Simple harmonic motion kinematics and conservation of energy.
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

Simple harmonic motion and conservation of momentum.
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

Conservation of energy only.
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

Conservation of momentum only.
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="false">

Conservation of energy and conservation of momentum.
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil8" correct="true">

Newton's laws and conservation of energy.
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil9" correct="false">

Newton's laws and conservation of momentum.
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil10" correct="false">

Newton's laws and constant-acceleration kinematics.
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="14">
        
          <p>
        <br/>
Part 2. 
At the instant ball passes its lowest position, which statements are true?
</p>
        
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="15" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                  The ball is in the state of equilibrium 
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="true">

                  The acceleration of the ball is directed upward
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                  The acceleration of the ball is directed downward
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                  The acceleration of the ball is directed to the left
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="true">

                  The force of tension in the string is at a maximum
                              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

The force of tension and the weight of the ball have the same magnitude
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="16">
        
          <p>
        <br/>
Part 3. 
If the speed of the ball at the lowest position is v, which equation is correct?
</p>
        
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="17" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                    \( mv^{2} = 2mgl\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} = 2mgl \cos \theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} = 2mgl \sin \theta\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="true">

                    \(mv^{2} = 2mgl(1 - \cos \theta)\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} = 2mgl(1 - \sin \theta)\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil6" correct="false">

m\(v^{2} = 2mgl(1 - \sin \theta)\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil7" correct="false">

m\(v^{2} = 2mgl(1 + \sin \theta)\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil8" correct="false">

m\(v^{2} = 2mgl(1 + \cos \theta)\)
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      <part loncapaid="18">
        
          <p>
        <br/>
Part 4. 
If the speed of the ball at the lowest position is v and the magnitude of the force of tension in the string is T, which equation is correct?
</p>
        
        <multiplechoiceresponse max="10" direction="vertical" randomize="yes" loncapaid="19" type="MultipleChoice">
          <choicegroup type="MultipleChoice">
            <choice location="random" name="foil1" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} /l = mg \)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil2" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} /l = T\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil3" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} /l = mg + T\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil4" correct="false">

                    \(mv^{2} /l = mg - T\)
              
            </choice>
            <choice location="random" name="foil5" correct="true">

                    \(mv^{2} /l = -mg + T\)
              
            </choice>
          </choicegroup>
        </multiplechoiceresponse>
      </part>
      
    </parameter>
  </problem>
</html>
